subsection.def:
plant
                    (裝置) includes any plant, equipment, gear,
                machinery, apparatus or appliance, or any part thereof;

reclamation
                    (填海工程) has the same meaning as in
                    section 2 of the Foreshore and Sea-bed (Reclamations) Ordinance (Cap. 127);

specified
                    (指明), in relation to a form or the
                particulars to be given on a form, means specified by the Authority;

paragraph.content:
any dusty materials remaining after a stockpile is removed shall be
                        wetted with water and cleared from the surface of roads or streets;
                        and

any dusty materials remaining after a stockpile is removed shall be
                        wetted with water and cleared from the surface of roads or streets;
                        and

subparagraph.content:
sprayed with water so as to maintain the entire surface wet, and
                            removed or backfilled or reinstated within 24 hours of the excavation or
                            unloading;

paragraph.content:
any dusty materials remaining after a stockpile is removed shall be
                        wetted with water and cleared from the surface of roads or streets;
                        and

the area where vehicle washing takes place and the section of the road
                        between the washing facilities and the exit point shall be paved with
                        concrete, bituminous materials or hardcores;
